1
00:00:30,070 --> 00:00:31,530
Now that we've made up.

2
00:00:31,710 --> 00:00:32,710
What are we now?

3
00:00:32,780 --> 00:00:36,200
Somporn and Anan's unfinished story.

4
00:00:36,260 --> 00:00:38,469
A writer can't abandon
their characters

5
00:00:38,470 --> 00:00:40,290
or their readers.

6
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:43,610
Please go ahead, sir.

7
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:44,960
Yes, thank you.

8
00:00:48,210 --> 00:00:49,780
"Good morning, everybody."

9
00:00:51,480 --> 00:00:54,600
"I am Somsak Prasitphithaya."

10
00:00:56,140 --> 00:00:58,910
"I'm an adventure novelist."

11
00:00:59,410 --> 00:01:03,830
"I write under my pen name:
Harn Chanprai."

12
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:09,190
I bet you young bucks
don't know who I am.

13
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:12,480
Anyway.

14
00:01:12,960 --> 00:01:16,340
Today, I bring you
very important news.

15
00:01:16,750 --> 00:01:17,760
"Actually,"

16
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:20,060
"the author of"

17
00:01:20,890 --> 00:01:22,510
"'Between Us in the Deep Forest'"

18
00:01:23,590 --> 00:01:25,660
"is not my nephew, Save."

19
00:01:28,090 --> 00:01:29,350
"I am the real author."

20
00:01:36,380 --> 00:01:37,420
I admit that

21
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:40,900
I couldn't bring myself
to tell the truth originally.

22
00:01:41,530 --> 00:01:43,710
The world I knew
when I was at my peak

23
00:01:44,660 --> 00:01:46,010
and the world today

24
00:01:47,090 --> 00:01:51,070
are... vastly different.

25
00:01:52,410 --> 00:01:54,720
I began writing this BL novel

26
00:01:55,300 --> 00:01:56,310
because.

27
00:01:58,450 --> 00:01:59,760
I needed to pay off my debt.

28
00:02:00,510 --> 00:02:01,880
When I first put pen to paper...

29
00:02:02,450 --> 00:02:03,450
Heh.

30
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:06,610
I was at war with myself.

31
00:02:08,140 --> 00:02:09,710
Nothing made sense.

32
00:02:10,670 --> 00:02:11,680
"But I learned,"

33
00:02:13,150 --> 00:02:15,720
"and kept writing
until the latest chapter."

34
00:02:17,170 --> 00:02:18,880
"In the end, I discovered"

35
00:02:20,050 --> 00:02:21,060
"that it was I"

36
00:02:23,110 --> 00:02:24,390
"who had been narrow-minded."

37
00:02:26,140 --> 00:02:27,160
"Because love,"

38
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:30,090
"in any form it takes,"

39
00:02:34,950 --> 00:02:36,370
is always beautiful.

40
00:02:39,620 --> 00:02:40,940
My nephew,

41
00:02:42,290 --> 00:02:43,370
his friend,

42
00:02:44,730 --> 00:02:45,730
my niece,

43
00:02:46,860 --> 00:02:49,270
all the children of Saeng Karun's,

44
00:02:50,970 --> 00:02:51,980
my own children,

45
00:02:53,310 --> 00:02:56,990
everyone I met
while searching for ideas,

46
00:02:57,790 --> 00:03:00,790
all of you readers...

47
00:03:01,450 --> 00:03:02,460
Oh...

48
00:03:03,220 --> 00:03:05,930
and the characters in this novel,

49
00:03:06,470 --> 00:03:08,040
Somporn and Anan.

50
00:03:09,220 --> 00:03:12,980
They all led me into
an entirely new world.

51
00:03:13,810 --> 00:03:15,770
And at last, I realized

52
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:18,460
that what I've done

53
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:20,630
is not wrong,

54
00:03:22,180 --> 00:03:26,080
but one of the most meaningful
and honorable things I've ever done.

55
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:29,310
And so I can now say
with the utmost pride...

56
00:03:30,670 --> 00:03:33,590
I am proud of this novel.

57
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:40,610
"Apologies to those
I did not tell the truth."

58
00:03:41,810 --> 00:03:43,480
Plainly, my age

59
00:03:45,090 --> 00:03:47,580
has not made me wise.

60
00:03:49,950 --> 00:03:50,980
"If anyone is at fault,"

61
00:03:52,570 --> 00:03:54,650
"it is I alone."

62
00:03:56,720 --> 00:03:59,880
"Please forgive my nephew."

63
00:04:02,290 --> 00:04:03,300
"He merely"

64
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:07,480
"did me a great kindness"

65
00:04:08,850 --> 00:04:12,750
"after I begged him
to pose as the author."

66
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:27,660
"I apologize, everyone."

67
00:04:29,630 --> 00:04:31,560
"I am partly responsible for this."

68
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:44,550
Excuse me. A question from a viewer.

69
00:04:44,790 --> 00:04:46,190
'What kind of debt, Grandpa?'

70
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:48,190
Certainly.

71
00:04:49,340 --> 00:04:51,170
I run a foster home.

72
00:04:51,450 --> 00:04:54,340
It's called Saeng Karun Foundation,

73
00:04:54,780 --> 00:04:58,070
a legacy passed down
from my grandfather.

74
00:04:58,650 --> 00:05:00,900
For several scores of years,

75
00:05:01,190 --> 00:05:04,070
the royalties from my novels
kept this place afloat.

76
00:05:04,340 --> 00:05:07,980
But with each new book,
the sales grew smaller and smaller.

77
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:11,380
Until, about thirty years ago,

78
00:05:12,660 --> 00:05:16,180
I had to start borrowing money
to meet the expenses of this place.

79
00:05:16,590 --> 00:05:20,130
Over time, that debt grew to
more than twelve million baht,

80
00:05:20,590 --> 00:05:22,490
owed to the bank.

81
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:26,500
Everyone here

82
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:30,250
has been doing their part
to help raise money.

83
00:05:34,820 --> 00:05:37,880
And I was determined
to write this novel

84
00:05:37,980 --> 00:05:40,930
to earn enough to pay off our debt

85
00:05:41,220 --> 00:05:45,540
and preserve this home
for the children who need it.

86
00:05:46,340 --> 00:05:48,090
"I hope you will"

87
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:52,170
"continue reading my novel."

88
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:54,570
"Thank you."

89
00:05:58,030 --> 00:06:00,230
- Very nice, Dad.
- Yeah.

90
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:01,810
Sit, sit.

91
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:04,810
Hmph.

92
00:06:09,310 --> 00:06:10,670
Feeling better, Grandpa?

93
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:12,460
The truth will save you.

94
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:15,890
Yeah. A load off my chest.

95
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,240
Mm-hmm.

96
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:20,190
So, any comments from the readers?

97
00:06:20,770 --> 00:06:23,550
I saw a few gripes and complaints.

98
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:25,770
Most of them were supportive.

99
00:06:26,190 --> 00:06:27,280
Whew.

100
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,480
Should've done this long ago.

101
00:06:29,550 --> 00:06:30,560
- Heh.
- Heh.

102
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:34,830
Trust me.
You'll grow more fans for sure.

103
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,250
Dad?

104
00:06:39,730 --> 00:06:42,480
What's wrong?
See how we are all relieved?

105
00:06:42,690 --> 00:06:43,950
Why the frown?

106
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:49,540
Dad, some readers are still upset.

107
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:52,340
They started a thread
and caused quite a stir.

108
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:54,980
And let's not forget
that Ajarn Thaworn.

109
00:06:55,260 --> 00:06:58,880
He criticized Save
right in front of you.

110
00:06:59,380 --> 00:07:00,380
Oy.

111
00:07:00,490 --> 00:07:03,110
I chose to face the truth.

112
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:05,410
I don't care about them.

113
00:07:08,660 --> 00:07:12,280
That's great, Father.
Don't waste your time on them.

114
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:14,630
Besides, I believe.

115
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:17,520
I'm doing the right thing.

116
00:07:17,870 --> 00:07:19,020
I have nothing to fear.

117
00:07:31,390 --> 00:07:33,460
I don't want to hide anymore.

118
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:35,810
You get me, right?

119
00:07:40,340 --> 00:07:42,990
I chose to face the truth.

120
00:07:43,980 --> 00:07:45,170
I don't care about them.

121
00:08:38,170 --> 00:08:39,180
Guy.

122
00:08:43,870 --> 00:08:44,930
Be my boyfriend.

123
00:08:50,020 --> 00:08:55,730
The world keeps
turning every day.

124
00:08:55,960 --> 00:09:01,010
And we keep turning in its play.

125
00:09:01,140 --> 00:09:04,320
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

126
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:07,070
We just might see
the world within.

127
00:09:07,140 --> 00:09:11,140
Let's walk together, day by day.

128
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:17,270
Come take the step,
what do you say?

129
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:26,670
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

130
00:09:26,950 --> 00:09:29,320
We just might see
the world within.

131
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:33,060
Let's walk together, day by day.

132
00:09:33,170 --> 00:09:41,170
Come take the step,
what do you say?

133
00:09:48,700 --> 00:09:51,550
Class, please turn to page 76.

134
00:10:08,410 --> 00:10:11,510
Hey, hey. Their hands are touching.

135
00:10:11,630 --> 00:10:14,760
- Hey.
- Woo.

136
00:10:15,220 --> 00:10:17,160
- Woo.
- Woo.

137
00:10:18,430 --> 00:10:21,190
What? What's going on?

138
00:10:24,220 --> 00:10:25,230
Hmm?

139
00:10:25,950 --> 00:10:28,000
Kornkan and Supawit.

140
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:29,760
Who forgot to bring the book?

141
00:10:30,260 --> 00:10:31,430
They didn't forget.

142
00:10:31,860 --> 00:10:33,600
They want to use the same book.

143
00:10:33,700 --> 00:10:36,710
- Tad, tad, dad.
- Yeah.

144
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:40,150
Alright. Quiet down. Quiet.

145
00:10:40,870 --> 00:10:43,290
Miss, may I go to the restroom?

146
00:10:47,170 --> 00:10:50,360
- Yeah...
- Restroom break?

147
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:53,910
Calm down. And read the book.

148
00:10:54,450 --> 00:10:55,910
I didn't say you two could go.

149
00:10:56,890 --> 00:10:58,840
Why did you shout
in front of everybody?

150
00:10:59,060 --> 00:11:01,810
Ow... you didn't want to
sneak around anymore.

151
00:11:02,260 --> 00:11:03,270
So I made it loud.

152
00:11:04,890 --> 00:11:05,900
Well, yeah.

153
00:11:06,590 --> 00:11:07,840
But there are different ways.

154
00:11:08,700 --> 00:11:09,900
Which way then?

155
00:11:11,390 --> 00:11:12,400
I don't know.

156
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:20,370
You're not okay?

157
00:11:22,060 --> 00:11:24,280
I'm okay. Just a bit embarrassed.

158
00:11:24,770 --> 00:11:27,620
I knew it. I knew you'd be okay.

159
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:31,740
So this means we're...

160
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:34,170
a couple?

161
00:12:20,630 --> 00:12:21,640
- Hey.
- Heh.

162
00:12:22,870 --> 00:12:25,140
- There you are.
- Well, well.

163
00:12:26,490 --> 00:12:27,530
Heh.

164
00:12:29,140 --> 00:12:31,160
Sorry I didn't tell you guys.

165
00:12:31,470 --> 00:12:33,720
Come on.
We've known for the longest time.

166
00:12:33,830 --> 00:12:34,840
Hmm?

167
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:38,370
You think you could
hide something this big?

168
00:12:40,530 --> 00:12:42,380
Hey, congrats.

169
00:12:42,790 --> 00:12:45,310
But if you want us to stop teasing,
dream on.

170
00:12:45,820 --> 00:12:47,850
Yeah, yeah. Whatever.

171
00:12:48,030 --> 00:12:49,559
Let's see you hold hands.

172
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:50,629
- Hey.
- Heh.

173
00:12:50,630 --> 00:12:52,560
You hold his hands.

174
00:12:52,950 --> 00:12:56,280
- Hey, hey. I see what's going on.
- My boys.

175
00:13:07,330 --> 00:13:08,340
Hey, Mom.

176
00:13:09,020 --> 00:13:12,110
Keep watching and
tell me who's coming on TV.

177
00:13:14,530 --> 00:13:16,420
Hmm... is it this channel?

178
00:13:16,590 --> 00:13:19,530
This doesn't seem right.
Is it today, really?

179
00:13:20,210 --> 00:13:23,060
Hold on. Just wait, Phi Sorn.

180
00:13:24,860 --> 00:13:26,510
Here, here. It's coming on.

181
00:13:26,910 --> 00:13:28,160
"Good morning, viewers."

182
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:30,270
"Speaking of the latest
online sensation,"

183
00:13:30,510 --> 00:13:34,310
"nothing has brought half of social
media to tears quite like this."

184
00:13:34,340 --> 00:13:36,669
"Khun Somsak has revealed himself"

185
00:13:36,670 --> 00:13:40,190
"as the author of
'Between Us in the Deep Forest.'"

186
00:13:40,240 --> 00:13:44,570
"Readers have been showering him
with support"

187
00:13:44,660 --> 00:13:47,830
"and admiration
for creating this BL novel,"

188
00:13:47,990 --> 00:13:50,770
"which has captured
the hearts of young readers."

189
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:54,810
- Hmm?
- A delivery?

190
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:56,330
I didn't order anything.

191
00:13:56,640 --> 00:13:58,450
Then, go see
who rang the bell, please.

192
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:18,240
Dad,

193
00:14:18,920 --> 00:14:19,930
how about a smile?

194
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:32,710
Dad, you have a guest.

195
00:14:38,940 --> 00:14:39,940
Ajarn?

196
00:14:44,130 --> 00:14:46,330
Can we talk for a bit, Khun Sak?

197
00:14:59,920 --> 00:15:04,340
I apologize for
holding back the truth.

198
00:15:05,020 --> 00:15:08,570
The moment I read the first page,
I knew you wrote it.

199
00:15:09,410 --> 00:15:12,860
I've read all your novels,
many times over.

200
00:15:13,190 --> 00:15:14,620
How could I not recognize it?

201
00:15:17,420 --> 00:15:20,970
Anyway, forgive me if my remarks
placed you in an awkward position.

202
00:15:21,680 --> 00:15:23,020
It's all right, sir.

203
00:15:24,030 --> 00:15:26,950
Two souls are seldom of one mind.

204
00:15:28,210 --> 00:15:30,330
I came today for no other reason

205
00:15:30,620 --> 00:15:33,860
than to have you hear it from me,
not through hearsay.

206
00:15:36,170 --> 00:15:36,810
Yes, sir.

207
00:15:37,150 --> 00:15:39,350
I will petition the Association

208
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:42,430
to strip you
of your senior membership.

209
00:15:43,650 --> 00:15:44,910
I fail to see

210
00:15:45,740 --> 00:15:48,700
that your novel is morally sound.

211
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:54,410
Do as you wish, sir.

212
00:15:55,340 --> 00:15:57,360
I shall not object.

213
00:15:58,160 --> 00:16:01,640
I would remind you of one thing,
however.

214
00:16:02,250 --> 00:16:04,130
We cannot stop the wheel of time.

215
00:16:04,680 --> 00:16:06,400
Of course, neither can I.

216
00:16:07,180 --> 00:16:10,120
Even if I must perish
with my generation,

217
00:16:10,620 --> 00:16:12,250
my convictions will not change.

218
00:16:15,710 --> 00:16:19,710
I've always admired
your convictions.

219
00:16:21,870 --> 00:16:23,000
My words are spent.

220
00:16:24,520 --> 00:16:26,040
Take care, Khun Sak.

221
00:16:30,190 --> 00:16:31,730
Likewise, sir.

222
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:54,990
So long, sir.

223
00:17:25,250 --> 00:17:28,030
Thanks for the news, Khun Chai.

224
00:17:31,630 --> 00:17:33,240
Writer's Association, Dad?

225
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:35,130
They're in a meeting.

226
00:17:36,020 --> 00:17:38,260
Don't worry
if they actually do it, Dad.

227
00:17:38,630 --> 00:17:40,370
No membership, no problem.

228
00:17:42,240 --> 00:17:43,250
Yes, Father.

229
00:17:43,790 --> 00:17:46,400
You don't need people like that,
clinging to the past.

230
00:17:47,030 --> 00:17:48,210
I couldn't care less.

231
00:17:52,310 --> 00:17:53,940
Try to relax, Father.

232
00:17:54,590 --> 00:17:56,820
The Association
may not rule in his favor.

233
00:17:58,750 --> 00:17:59,760
Really, Dad.

234
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:02,210
You're better off
without a friend like that.

235
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:04,160
Easy for you to say.

236
00:18:04,890 --> 00:18:06,910
They've been friends
for half their lives.

237
00:18:09,660 --> 00:18:12,720
We were the closest of friends.

238
00:18:14,450 --> 00:18:15,760
But I suppose that is no more.

239
00:18:32,130 --> 00:18:35,210
Save, here you are. Just in time.

240
00:18:35,520 --> 00:18:38,400
I've got good ideas
for the new chapter.

241
00:18:42,500 --> 00:18:43,500
Okay.

242
00:18:48,390 --> 00:18:50,590
Grandpa, I've got news.

243
00:18:51,980 --> 00:18:53,270
Good or bad?

244
00:18:54,380 --> 00:18:56,980
Guy and I are officially a couple.

245
00:18:57,800 --> 00:19:00,090
- Officially?
- Yeah.

246
00:19:00,570 --> 00:19:02,880
- You two patched things up?
- Mm-hmm.

247
00:19:03,820 --> 00:19:05,660
We just made it official today.

248
00:19:05,990 --> 00:19:07,290
Isn't it too soon?

249
00:19:07,510 --> 00:19:09,820
No way. It's been too long.

250
00:19:14,560 --> 00:19:15,940
You heard of protection, right?

251
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:19,150
Hmph... what are you talking about?

252
00:19:21,450 --> 00:19:22,510
Just making sure.

253
00:19:23,070 --> 00:19:25,780
So what now? The two of you
are at which stage?

254
00:19:27,190 --> 00:19:30,350
We're not going so fast.
Just got started.

255
00:19:31,090 --> 00:19:33,350
Anyway, I'm happy for you.

256
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:36,060
Don't upset him again.

257
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:37,560
I won't.

258
00:19:38,130 --> 00:19:40,530
Back to the novel.
What was the last chapter?

259
00:19:41,520 --> 00:19:42,650
Fifteen.

260
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:44,160
Okey.

261
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:45,800
Dokey.

262
00:19:48,850 --> 00:19:51,130
Oh, your eyes. How are they?

263
00:19:52,020 --> 00:19:53,350
Still blurry.

264
00:19:55,660 --> 00:19:56,810
But I'll scrape by.

265
00:20:00,630 --> 00:20:01,830
And then...

266
00:20:03,230 --> 00:20:04,230
Ow?

267
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:09,020
"Phi Cha, Climax Studio."

268
00:20:09,060 --> 00:20:10,120
Hey...

269
00:20:11,830 --> 00:20:14,050
- Yes, hi.
- Hi, Save.

270
00:20:14,210 --> 00:20:17,970
Are you free for the audition
this Saturday?

271
00:20:24,020 --> 00:20:25,470
No idea what they'll have me do.

272
00:20:25,840 --> 00:20:28,950
- What do I need?
- You need talent.

273
00:20:30,060 --> 00:20:31,600
Thanks, but I have none.

274
00:20:32,310 --> 00:20:34,140
Anything, really. Just show them.

275
00:20:34,420 --> 00:20:36,650
Maybe they just want to see
you're not shy.

276
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:39,110
A triple front flip?

277
00:20:39,510 --> 00:20:40,770
A jump through a flaming hoop?

278
00:20:42,380 --> 00:20:43,600
Go for it if you can.

279
00:20:51,730 --> 00:20:53,780
Hey, how about coming with me?

280
00:20:54,370 --> 00:20:56,490
Why? Stage fright?

281
00:20:57,870 --> 00:20:59,140
I've never done this before.

282
00:20:59,820 --> 00:21:01,420
Yeah, I'll go with you.

283
00:21:02,130 --> 00:21:03,920
- For real?
- You got it.

284
00:21:06,810 --> 00:21:09,220
Awesome. My boyfriend's
coming to my audition.

285
00:21:09,260 --> 00:21:11,130
I don't know who else to ask.

286
00:21:11,820 --> 00:21:14,990
Come on. You'd ask me to come with
anyway.

287
00:21:16,310 --> 00:21:17,310
You're right.

288
00:21:41,750 --> 00:21:42,760
Ready, Save?

289
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:44,610
Uh...

290
00:21:45,760 --> 00:21:47,130
Kind of. Heh.

291
00:21:48,410 --> 00:21:50,210
Oh, and is this Guy?

292
00:21:50,730 --> 00:21:52,640
You both did livestreams
selling snacks.

293
00:21:53,990 --> 00:21:55,220
Oh, this is him.

294
00:21:56,170 --> 00:21:57,980
Sorry, he's the shy type.

295
00:21:58,880 --> 00:22:01,530
How about...
you both do the audition?

296
00:22:01,910 --> 00:22:02,910
Ha?

297
00:22:03,560 --> 00:22:04,970
Uhm. Is that a good idea?

298
00:22:05,460 --> 00:22:07,240
I'm just here...
to keep him company.

299
00:22:08,280 --> 00:22:10,000
Well, you're here.
Might as well try.

300
00:22:12,700 --> 00:22:15,280
Up to you. I've got your back.

301
00:22:24,340 --> 00:22:25,530
Good morning, everyone.

302
00:22:27,190 --> 00:22:28,860
What do you want to show us today?

303
00:22:29,820 --> 00:22:30,830
Singing talent.

304
00:22:31,190 --> 00:22:32,200
Are you ready?

305
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:34,810
The floor is yours.

306
00:22:38,930 --> 00:22:41,160
The clock keeps ticking,
never still.

307
00:22:41,650 --> 00:22:43,720
As time rolls on
beyond our will.

308
00:22:44,270 --> 00:22:48,360
The seasons turn
in endless style.

309
00:22:49,460 --> 00:22:51,520
We break down and cry.

310
00:22:52,130 --> 00:22:54,230
Sometimes we smile.

311
00:22:54,280 --> 00:22:57,780
Nothing stands still,
even if we try.

312
00:22:58,650 --> 00:23:02,080
Let us be real,
not dreaming away,

313
00:23:02,440 --> 00:23:06,090
We'll walk in the light
of a new day.

314
00:23:06,350 --> 00:23:11,180
No one can tell
what tomorrow may say.

315
00:23:11,250 --> 00:23:13,460
Wherever the gentle wind blows,

316
00:23:13,540 --> 00:23:16,190
let our hearts flow,
soft and slow.

317
00:23:16,320 --> 00:23:20,350
And land where
our hearts both grow.

318
00:23:21,300 --> 00:23:27,320
The world keeps
turning every day.

319
00:23:27,420 --> 00:23:32,670
And we keep turning in its play.

320
00:23:32,770 --> 00:23:36,270
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

321
00:23:36,410 --> 00:23:38,930
We just might see
the world within.

322
00:23:38,980 --> 00:23:43,010
Let's walk together, day by day.

323
00:23:43,130 --> 00:23:47,340
Come take the step,
what do you say?

324
00:23:55,560 --> 00:23:57,360
And, Guy, go right ahead.

325
00:23:58,160 --> 00:23:59,950
- Please take a break, Save.
- Sure.

326
00:24:16,340 --> 00:24:17,350
Singing talent too?

327
00:24:19,340 --> 00:24:21,380
Ow? What did you bring for us?

328
00:24:55,750 --> 00:24:56,750
Guy.

329
00:24:57,590 --> 00:24:58,600
You think I'll make it?

330
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:01,010
Sure you will.

331
00:25:01,570 --> 00:25:03,090
You had a star-like aura.

332
00:25:06,020 --> 00:25:07,030
I don't believe you.

333
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:10,060
Your soccer juggling just killed.

334
00:25:11,220 --> 00:25:13,930
Me? I didn't do anything...

335
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:15,630
just went in there to see you.

336
00:25:17,080 --> 00:25:18,570
You were impressive.

337
00:25:19,010 --> 00:25:21,520
They're in luck if they pick you.

338
00:25:27,060 --> 00:25:30,080
Well, well. Are you excited?

339
00:25:30,630 --> 00:25:33,810
Oh-ho. Very much so.
This is our first time.

340
00:25:34,030 --> 00:25:35,340
Oh, really?

341
00:25:35,680 --> 00:25:37,880
For your first audition,
you're doing amazing.

342
00:25:38,490 --> 00:25:39,500
Wow.

343
00:25:39,900 --> 00:25:43,730
We're all impressed
by your potential.

344
00:25:44,080 --> 00:25:48,420
Next time, we'd like you
to make up a script

345
00:25:48,460 --> 00:25:50,130
and do a cold scene.
Sound good?

346
00:25:50,630 --> 00:25:51,980
Of course. Okay.

347
00:25:55,260 --> 00:25:56,270
Uh.

348
00:25:56,920 --> 00:25:58,410
Yes, okay.

349
00:25:59,040 --> 00:26:00,500
- Heh.
- You got it.

350
00:26:00,600 --> 00:26:02,390
Great. Just great.

351
00:26:02,550 --> 00:26:03,550
Thanks.

352
00:26:14,690 --> 00:26:15,880
You just had an audi...

353
00:26:17,390 --> 00:26:18,600
audition, right?

354
00:26:18,810 --> 00:26:19,620
Mm-hmm.

355
00:26:19,621 --> 00:26:22,660
They've produced
several hit series.

356
00:26:23,340 --> 00:26:26,540
And they want us to sign
with the studio.

357
00:26:28,160 --> 00:26:29,810
You sure they're not cons?

358
00:26:29,940 --> 00:26:31,890
No, they are the real deal.

359
00:26:32,110 --> 00:26:34,760
See, if they sign us,
we could star in a series.

360
00:26:34,810 --> 00:26:35,430
Hmm?

361
00:26:35,730 --> 00:26:39,250
Can you act?
Stop stammering would be a start.

362
00:26:39,450 --> 00:26:42,250
Grandpa, my diction is impeccable.

363
00:26:43,620 --> 00:26:44,650
You sure you can do it?

364
00:26:45,150 --> 00:26:47,950
Well, I'll try.
Opportunity has come knocking.

365
00:26:48,180 --> 00:26:50,670
If I make it big,
there's serious money in it.

366
00:26:50,810 --> 00:26:52,780
Hmph. You're all talk.

367
00:26:52,940 --> 00:26:56,360
Did you rope Guy into this?

368
00:26:56,910 --> 00:27:00,740
No, sir. It looked like fun,
so I jumped in.

369
00:27:00,900 --> 00:27:02,750
- Mm-hmm.
- Hmm. I'm glad.

370
00:27:03,500 --> 00:27:07,800
They want us to rehearse a scene
for the next audition.

371
00:27:08,550 --> 00:27:11,480
Guy suggested we use one
from your novel.

372
00:27:13,380 --> 00:27:14,390
May we, sir?

373
00:27:15,630 --> 00:27:17,890
You mean Somporn and Anan?

374
00:27:18,170 --> 00:27:19,170
Exactly.

375
00:27:19,790 --> 00:27:21,410
Are you really up to it?

376
00:27:21,660 --> 00:27:25,070
The characters are too far removed
from what you are now.

377
00:27:28,120 --> 00:27:30,610
We'll have you to coach us, sir.

378
00:27:31,180 --> 00:27:32,310
Coach?

379
00:27:35,030 --> 00:27:37,410
I've never coached
or directed anyone before.

380
00:27:37,840 --> 00:27:38,840
I can't do it.

381
00:27:39,160 --> 00:27:39,990
Yes, you can.

382
00:27:40,040 --> 00:27:43,110
Just explain the characters,
their thoughts and emotions.

383
00:27:43,140 --> 00:27:45,550
Then we'll bring Somporn and Anan

384
00:27:45,800 --> 00:27:47,910
from the pages to life.

385
00:27:48,460 --> 00:27:49,470
Really?

386
00:27:50,630 --> 00:27:51,630
Mm-hmm.

387
00:27:52,200 --> 00:27:53,230
So...

388
00:27:54,160 --> 00:27:55,370
we have your permission?

389
00:27:57,310 --> 00:27:58,340
- Yeah.
- Hey.

390
00:27:58,380 --> 00:27:59,730
- Hey.
- Yay.

391
00:27:59,980 --> 00:28:01,050
Listen, you two.

392
00:28:01,700 --> 00:28:04,480
Promise you'll do
the characters justice.

393
00:28:04,810 --> 00:28:07,360
My name is riding on this.

394
00:28:07,510 --> 00:28:09,810
- Of course. We'll do our best.
- Yes, sir.

395
00:28:09,840 --> 00:28:11,530
- Heh.
- Hmph.

396
00:28:11,880 --> 00:28:12,880
Then it's settled.

397
00:28:13,120 --> 00:28:15,980
I'll help coach you and your friend.

398
00:28:16,010 --> 00:28:17,960
Your boyfriend, that is.

399
00:28:19,050 --> 00:28:20,450
In exchange,

400
00:28:20,610 --> 00:28:24,549
you will help me type up
the remaining chapters.

401
00:28:24,550 --> 00:28:27,200
The finale is around the corner.
Okay?

402
00:28:27,380 --> 00:28:28,390
You got it, Grandpa.

403
00:29:07,880 --> 00:29:13,190
My, my. I'm about to become
the mother of a TV star.

404
00:29:13,820 --> 00:29:17,520
I'll need new glamorous outfits
to go on TV with, huh?

405
00:29:18,170 --> 00:29:20,500
Not so fast, Mom.
We're not stars yet.

406
00:29:20,690 --> 00:29:22,560
See? This is why
I don't tell you stuff.

407
00:29:23,450 --> 00:29:26,910
Listen to him.
Huh. Nothing I do is right.

408
00:29:27,660 --> 00:29:29,230
Guy, is he always like this?

409
00:29:30,270 --> 00:29:34,440
Save, don't tease her like that.
She's just so happy for you.

410
00:29:35,420 --> 00:29:36,960
Sure, take her side.

411
00:29:37,240 --> 00:29:38,240
Heh.

412
00:29:38,340 --> 00:29:40,980
Hey, Save.
You're gonna become an actor

413
00:29:41,560 --> 00:29:42,670
without even asking me?

414
00:29:44,970 --> 00:29:45,970
Do I have to?

415
00:29:46,620 --> 00:29:49,500
Ow, you're entering showbiz;
what about school?

416
00:29:49,820 --> 00:29:52,180
Everybody studies and works
at the same time now.

417
00:29:52,470 --> 00:29:54,520
But if you can't maintain
your honors standing?

418
00:29:55,550 --> 00:29:56,780
Ow, Dad?

419
00:29:57,320 --> 00:29:59,910
Will you let them
run their own lives?

420
00:30:00,270 --> 00:30:02,740
Don't be a grown-up
they don't look up to.

421
00:30:03,730 --> 00:30:04,730
Okay?

422
00:30:05,690 --> 00:30:07,630
- Okay?
- Heh.

423
00:30:11,900 --> 00:30:15,410
My best wish to both of you, okay?

424
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:17,590
Of course, Mother.

425
00:30:17,960 --> 00:30:19,620
So sweet. Hehe.

426
00:30:31,140 --> 00:30:32,140
Let me see.

427
00:30:33,180 --> 00:30:35,630
- Hey. It's growing.
- Mine too.

428
00:30:38,090 --> 00:30:39,090
Oh, no.

429
00:30:39,660 --> 00:30:41,780
Everyone else's is growing but mine.

430
00:30:43,470 --> 00:30:44,640
Whose fault is that?

431
00:30:44,870 --> 00:30:47,090
Jingjai, did you forget
the fertilizer?

432
00:30:47,290 --> 00:30:49,510
No, no. I did fertilize the pot.

433
00:30:51,730 --> 00:30:54,890
Liar. We'll be short of vegetables
because of you.

434
00:30:59,370 --> 00:31:00,930
Did you have to run your mouth?

435
00:31:01,150 --> 00:31:02,930
How do you know she forgot?

436
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:05,480
And even if she did,
couldn't you tell her nicely?

437
00:31:05,700 --> 00:31:07,530
You didn't have to be so mean.

438
00:31:09,370 --> 00:31:12,380
Right. There are vegetables
in those other plots.

439
00:31:13,160 --> 00:31:16,320
We never yelled at you when
you forgot to water these plants.

440
00:31:31,360 --> 00:31:35,520
Jingjai, don't mind him.
He always puts others down.

441
00:31:37,320 --> 00:31:40,270
Yeah. Don't let it bother you.

442
00:31:42,410 --> 00:31:46,900
You must learn to handle mean kids,
so they can't bully you.

443
00:31:47,740 --> 00:31:48,750
Thanks.

444
00:31:54,620 --> 00:31:57,540
Ever since I came here,
you've been the only ones

445
00:31:57,840 --> 00:31:59,330
who look after me.

446
00:32:02,160 --> 00:32:03,800
Friends support each other.

447
00:32:04,640 --> 00:32:05,650
Friends?

448
00:32:06,070 --> 00:32:07,080
Do you

449
00:32:08,850 --> 00:32:10,830
think of me as a friend?

450
00:32:14,380 --> 00:32:17,520
Ever since we let you
read BL novels with us.

451
00:32:20,850 --> 00:32:22,040
Thanks a lot.

452
00:32:22,120 --> 00:32:24,450
You make me want to
stay here forever.

453
00:32:36,140 --> 00:32:37,200
Huk. Huk.

454
00:32:37,300 --> 00:32:39,680
Huk. Huk. Hngh. Hngh.

455
00:32:39,950 --> 00:32:41,290
Don't cry.

456
00:32:42,250 --> 00:32:43,250
Don't cry now.

457
00:32:44,950 --> 00:32:45,960
Huh.

458
00:32:49,900 --> 00:32:51,370
Crying again.

459
00:32:52,760 --> 00:32:54,260
You should stop that.

460
00:32:58,760 --> 00:33:00,590
I have one more thing to tell you.

461
00:33:01,910 --> 00:33:02,910
What is it?

462
00:33:05,790 --> 00:33:08,990
I actually forgot to
put fertilizer in his pot.

463
00:33:09,620 --> 00:33:11,240
- Jingjai.
- Jingjai.

464
00:33:22,970 --> 00:33:25,800
"Available in print in 15 days.
Pre-order now."

465
00:33:28,500 --> 00:33:30,110
"Posting."

466
00:33:46,820 --> 00:33:49,940
Your pre-orders have now
passed ten thousand.

467
00:33:51,710 --> 00:33:54,470
Really? This morning, they were just
around eight thousand.

468
00:33:56,030 --> 00:33:57,620
They just keep coming in.

469
00:33:59,630 --> 00:34:00,630
Grandpa.

470
00:34:02,710 --> 00:34:03,710
Very well.

471
00:34:04,760 --> 00:34:07,590
I'll entrust my book
to your publishing house.

472
00:34:07,800 --> 00:34:10,690
Yes, sir.
I am truly honored.

473
00:34:10,850 --> 00:34:13,250
I'll make sure
everything goes perfectly.

474
00:34:13,410 --> 00:34:15,260
Not a single typo.

475
00:34:15,480 --> 00:34:17,750
Well. Thanks a million.

476
00:34:18,380 --> 00:34:19,480
Please excuse us.

477
00:34:20,590 --> 00:34:21,850
Very well, sir.

478
00:34:23,380 --> 00:34:25,090
Alright. Let's get back and write.

479
00:34:26,360 --> 00:34:27,480
- Thank you.
- Yes.

480
00:34:46,220 --> 00:34:49,390
"Guys and girls. Pre-order
Between Us and the Deep Forest yet?"

481
00:34:49,520 --> 00:34:51,629
In just fourteen days,

482
00:34:51,630 --> 00:34:56,210
we'll dive into the pages
of Somporn and Anan's story.

483
00:34:56,630 --> 00:35:00,520
Can't wait to see which character
postcard comes with my copy.

484
00:35:00,710 --> 00:35:03,070
Every copy includes one,
so why wait?

485
00:35:03,090 --> 00:35:05,350
Pre-order your copy today.

486
00:35:09,840 --> 00:35:12,020
Their quest was never for

487
00:35:13,910 --> 00:35:16,880
riches untold or glittering stones,

488
00:35:17,380 --> 00:35:18,890
but for what lay between them:

489
00:35:19,900 --> 00:35:21,140
an important friend

490
00:35:22,080 --> 00:35:23,180
in times of need.

491
00:35:25,510 --> 00:35:27,340
Not a friend to the end.

492
00:35:30,410 --> 00:35:32,890
He never wanted his friend to die.

493
00:35:34,810 --> 00:35:37,130
So, for lack of a better word,

494
00:35:37,680 --> 00:35:39,060
they were simply "friends."

495
00:35:39,910 --> 00:35:41,200
He wanted only to

496
00:35:44,050 --> 00:35:45,830
keep Anan in his life.

497
00:35:46,830 --> 00:35:48,520
Distance did not trouble him.

498
00:35:50,390 --> 00:35:51,860
What strengthened their bond

499
00:35:52,590 --> 00:35:53,910
was knowing Anan was safe.

500
00:35:55,490 --> 00:35:57,160
Should harm ever come to Anan,

501
00:35:57,770 --> 00:36:00,700
he would wish to be the first

502
00:36:02,510 --> 00:36:03,520
to stand at his side.

503
00:36:05,450 --> 00:36:07,070
Even if he had nothing to offer,

504
00:36:08,730 --> 00:36:12,590
his unsure presence
would still matter.

505
00:36:34,180 --> 00:36:36,810
The world around him shifted,

506
00:36:38,010 --> 00:36:40,340
as though touched by a silent spell.

507
00:36:40,600 --> 00:36:43,480
Only the flutter of two hearts

508
00:36:43,980 --> 00:36:47,200
kept softly beating as one.

509
00:36:48,100 --> 00:36:52,810
Their eyes met one final time

510
00:36:53,660 --> 00:36:57,450
before what remained of Somporn

511
00:36:58,350 --> 00:37:03,150
ventured deeper into the forest

512
00:37:04,040 --> 00:37:07,160
that knew no bounds.

513
00:37:23,650 --> 00:37:25,120
The End.

514
00:37:31,080 --> 00:37:33,380
"The End."

515
00:37:39,680 --> 00:37:40,950
Very touching.

516
00:37:41,960 --> 00:37:42,970
Mm-hmm.

517
00:37:44,850 --> 00:37:46,070
You glazing me?

518
00:37:46,730 --> 00:37:47,740
No glaze.

519
00:37:48,380 --> 00:37:50,730
Look at you, keeping up
with the latest slang.

520
00:37:51,200 --> 00:37:52,630
Snow taught me.

521
00:37:55,270 --> 00:37:56,270
And...

522
00:37:57,780 --> 00:37:59,130
that was the end, huh?

523
00:37:59,810 --> 00:38:02,980
Why? You want a sequel?

524
00:38:03,670 --> 00:38:04,680
Not that.

525
00:38:05,320 --> 00:38:06,480
It feels...

526
00:38:07,760 --> 00:38:08,770
sudden

527
00:38:09,880 --> 00:38:11,620
after several months
with this novel.

528
00:38:13,980 --> 00:38:14,980
Same here.

529
00:38:16,260 --> 00:38:18,160
It's a sudden emptiness

530
00:38:18,580 --> 00:38:20,900
every time
I write "The End" on a novel.

531
00:38:22,450 --> 00:38:25,960
I can't wait to publish this...
masterpiece.

532
00:38:26,280 --> 00:38:28,910
Yeah, well. I owe you big time.

533
00:38:29,670 --> 00:38:32,860
Your painstaking work

534
00:38:33,760 --> 00:38:37,420
has saved me from serious rehab.

535
00:38:38,770 --> 00:38:40,390
I owe you one too.

536
00:38:40,880 --> 00:38:41,950
For not bailing out.

537
00:38:43,260 --> 00:38:45,330
See? My faith in you has paid off.

538
00:38:45,560 --> 00:38:46,560
Yeah.

539
00:38:47,040 --> 00:38:48,920
Let's call it a night.

540
00:38:49,430 --> 00:38:50,440
I'm retiring.

541
00:38:51,060 --> 00:38:52,060
Yeah. Sack time.

542
00:38:52,580 --> 00:38:55,680
Tomorrow, I'll read it again
before sending to Phi Phuri.

543
00:38:58,350 --> 00:38:59,540
Hmph.

544
00:39:03,540 --> 00:39:04,550
All good, Grandpa.

545
00:39:09,290 --> 00:39:10,300
Here.

546
00:39:11,390 --> 00:39:12,540
Hmph.

547
00:39:14,270 --> 00:39:15,480
Okay. Here you go.

548
00:39:21,460 --> 00:39:22,460
Okay.

549
00:39:23,100 --> 00:39:24,450
Scoot over a bit.

550
00:39:24,840 --> 00:39:26,590
- Back?
- Forward, yeah.

551
00:39:27,560 --> 00:39:29,520
Alright. Gently.

552
00:39:42,790 --> 00:39:44,400
- Good night.
- Heh.

553
00:39:44,740 --> 00:39:45,740
Good night.

554
00:41:41,020 --> 00:41:42,230
Sit here, Dad.

555
00:41:46,500 --> 00:41:47,560
- Dad.
- Hmm?

556
00:41:47,740 --> 00:41:51,010
What would you like
to celebrate with?

557
00:41:51,510 --> 00:41:53,590
Now that you've finished the novel.

558
00:41:54,020 --> 00:41:55,360
Anything will do.

559
00:41:55,950 --> 00:41:58,710
Everything tastes
ten times better now.

560
00:41:59,910 --> 00:42:03,960
Sorn, have you checked
the deposit on the pre-orders?

561
00:42:05,210 --> 00:42:06,210
I have.

562
00:42:06,460 --> 00:42:08,370
It should cover
several debt payments.

563
00:42:08,770 --> 00:42:13,110
Good. Once it's published,
we'll make a lot more money.

564
00:42:13,910 --> 00:42:16,600
Yeah. You're the best Dad ever.

565
00:42:17,020 --> 00:42:19,920
Soon, we can pay off all of it.

566
00:42:19,960 --> 00:42:22,080
- Heh. Mwah.
- Hey!

567
00:42:22,270 --> 00:42:25,590
- What are you, five years old?
- Heh.

568
00:42:26,550 --> 00:42:28,390
Grandpa, come here.

569
00:42:42,920 --> 00:42:44,640
"Microsoft Word:
Error accessing file."

570
00:42:44,740 --> 00:42:47,130
Can't open the files.
Don't know what's wrong.

571
00:42:47,300 --> 00:42:48,300
Hmm?

572
00:42:48,730 --> 00:42:50,470
Can't open any of them?

573
00:42:50,860 --> 00:42:52,090
Just the last two chapters.

574
00:42:55,310 --> 00:42:57,140
Well, I'm headed to a repair shop.

575
00:42:58,060 --> 00:43:01,060
Hey, wait.
I thought you had an audition.

576
00:43:01,960 --> 00:43:03,230
Yeah... but...

577
00:43:04,680 --> 00:43:06,490
Khun Phuri is waiting for our files.

578
00:43:06,880 --> 00:43:08,120
I'll hurry back.

579
00:43:18,870 --> 00:43:20,050
Oh, here's Save.

580
00:43:21,450 --> 00:43:22,450
Ready for the audition?

581
00:43:22,640 --> 00:43:25,400
No, I can't go yet.
I need to fix my laptop.

582
00:43:25,910 --> 00:43:27,600
I couldn't open the files.

583
00:43:27,910 --> 00:43:30,020
Ow.
Aren't they expecting them by ten?

584
00:43:30,050 --> 00:43:31,060
Exactly, Mom.

585
00:43:32,360 --> 00:43:33,370
You go first, Guy.

586
00:43:33,850 --> 00:43:34,860
Hold up.

587
00:43:35,220 --> 00:43:36,230
We go together.

588
00:43:36,700 --> 00:43:38,950
- It could take long.
- It doesn't matter.

589
00:43:39,230 --> 00:43:40,480
I go wherever you go.

590
00:43:41,840 --> 00:43:44,820
- Then we go to a repair shop first.
- Okay.

591
00:43:46,280 --> 00:43:47,500
I'll be back, Mother.

592
00:43:47,840 --> 00:43:49,900
Yeah, yeah. Hope you get it fixed.

593
00:43:51,570 --> 00:43:52,840
Be careful on the road.

594
00:44:06,520 --> 00:44:07,520
Put it there.

595
00:44:17,330 --> 00:44:19,010
Be safe.

596
00:44:23,530 --> 00:44:25,080
Get it fixed.

597
00:44:37,380 --> 00:44:39,210
"Phuri, Publisher."

598
00:44:44,680 --> 00:44:45,690
Hello?

599
00:44:45,760 --> 00:44:46,770
How's it going, sir?

600
00:44:47,050 --> 00:44:50,090
We've been expecting your file
as discussed.

601
00:44:50,590 --> 00:44:54,230
Can I have a little more time
to fix it up?

602
00:44:54,880 --> 00:44:58,910
If we could help,
my proofreaders are standing by.

603
00:44:59,630 --> 00:45:01,460
I see. Great help.

604
00:45:02,070 --> 00:45:04,490
Let me give it a final touch.
Okay?

605
00:45:04,630 --> 00:45:08,410
Alright, I won't bother you.
Email me as soon as you can.

606
00:45:26,680 --> 00:45:28,960
- Dad, it's Save.
- Yeah?

607
00:45:30,060 --> 00:45:32,240
The hard drive failed.
Unrecoverable.

608
00:45:32,810 --> 00:45:35,730
What? What are we gonna do?

609
00:45:35,810 --> 00:45:38,170
Guy said his expert uncle
would take another look.

610
00:45:38,380 --> 00:45:40,440
Yeah, pass it along.

611
00:45:40,880 --> 00:45:42,760
Call us if he finds anything.

612
00:45:54,090 --> 00:45:55,400
I'm sorry, Grandpa.

613
00:45:56,080 --> 00:45:58,800
My uncle says there's really
nothing he can do.

614
00:45:58,830 --> 00:45:59,830
- What?
- What?

615
00:46:00,860 --> 00:46:02,520
So what do we do now?

616
00:46:06,080 --> 00:46:07,560
We'll have to type it up again.

617
00:46:07,920 --> 00:46:10,440
What? Type it up again?

618
00:46:11,430 --> 00:46:14,080
Do you even remember, Dad?

619
00:46:18,230 --> 00:46:19,230
Huh.

620
00:46:19,360 --> 00:46:21,400
There's really no other way?

621
00:46:21,800 --> 00:46:23,680
Well, that's just our luck.

622
00:46:24,790 --> 00:46:26,150
It had to fail now of all times.

623
00:46:33,710 --> 00:46:34,710
Fine.

624
00:46:35,790 --> 00:46:37,050
I'll rewrite them.

625
00:46:37,210 --> 00:46:38,210
What?

626
00:46:39,330 --> 00:46:41,320
I'll ask Khun Phuri
for an extension.

627
00:46:41,740 --> 00:46:44,570
No, no.
His people are waiting on this.

628
00:46:44,880 --> 00:46:49,080
In over thirty years of my career,
I've never missed a deadline.

629
00:46:49,780 --> 00:46:52,870
We're getting this to them
by the end of the day.

630
00:48:59,100 --> 00:49:00,140
- Mm-hmm.
- Phi Sorn.

631
00:49:00,330 --> 00:49:01,110
He...

632
00:49:01,140 --> 00:49:03,720
You go take the order. It's my turn.

633
00:49:03,820 --> 00:49:05,680
Wait, wait. He...

634
00:49:06,000 --> 00:49:07,266
- It's okay, Dad.
- Take the order.

635
00:49:07,290 --> 00:49:08,420
- He, he.
- Yeah.

636
00:49:34,080 --> 00:49:35,360
I just came back to see you.

637
00:49:36,390 --> 00:49:37,680
No word of love.

638
00:49:38,440 --> 00:49:39,800
No confession.

639
00:49:40,130 --> 00:49:42,070
Hmm... keep reading.

640
00:49:42,120 --> 00:49:44,120
Hey, is there anything
your wife can't do?

641
00:49:44,760 --> 00:49:45,340
Ow?

642
00:49:45,360 --> 00:49:46,600
Heh.

643
00:49:49,020 --> 00:49:50,220
Keep going, Father.

644
00:49:50,240 --> 00:49:51,140
Yeah.

645
00:49:51,170 --> 00:49:52,240
No confession.

646
00:49:53,450 --> 00:49:54,490
Hello.

647
00:49:54,560 --> 00:49:57,520
Hi, we've got the second round
audition today. Right?

648
00:49:58,200 --> 00:49:59,400
Yeah, I remember that.

649
00:49:59,810 --> 00:50:01,870
I'm rushing through
this brutal traffic.

650
00:50:02,050 --> 00:50:03,360
I'm on my way.

651
00:50:13,300 --> 00:50:14,740
Move to the next line.

652
00:50:14,940 --> 00:50:15,940
Mm-hmm.

653
00:50:17,570 --> 00:50:19,600
And, uh...

654
00:50:21,640 --> 00:50:23,160
And Somporn...

655
00:50:25,990 --> 00:50:27,830
"Phuri, Publisher."

656
00:50:28,380 --> 00:50:29,380
Dad.

657
00:50:30,430 --> 00:50:31,430
Khun Phuri's calling.

658
00:50:33,190 --> 00:50:34,320
Tell him to hold on.

659
00:50:40,510 --> 00:50:41,510
Yes, sir.

660
00:50:41,540 --> 00:50:42,920
Still nothing from you yet.

661
00:50:43,130 --> 00:50:45,560
Uh, Dad asked me to tell you...

662
00:50:46,400 --> 00:50:47,460
just wait a bit, please.

663
00:50:48,490 --> 00:50:49,490
Hello?

664
00:50:52,940 --> 00:50:53,940
Dad.

665
00:50:55,360 --> 00:50:56,400
What's next, Grandpa?

666
00:50:57,560 --> 00:50:58,560
Give me a moment.

667
00:50:58,920 --> 00:51:02,040
Composing a line isn't
like tossing a coin.

668
00:51:06,060 --> 00:51:09,330
Oh, oh. I got it. Was it like this?

669
00:51:10,340 --> 00:51:13,120
'before what remained of Somporn'

670
00:51:13,880 --> 00:51:15,839
Yes, type that.

671
00:51:15,840 --> 00:51:17,120
- Go with that?
- Yeah.

672
00:51:22,320 --> 00:51:23,320
The End.

673
00:51:23,790 --> 00:51:25,880
- Hey.
- Yes, we're done.

674
00:51:28,460 --> 00:51:30,450
Oh, did you save it, Save?

675
00:51:31,160 --> 00:51:32,160
Already did, Mom.

676
00:51:32,760 --> 00:51:36,280
- Then send these out.
- Okay.

677
00:51:37,700 --> 00:51:40,230
"Send Email."

678
00:51:40,480 --> 00:51:41,480
"Sending."

679
00:51:43,910 --> 00:51:45,200
- Yes.
- Yes.

680
00:51:47,750 --> 00:51:48,920
Okay, brilliant.

681
00:51:49,910 --> 00:51:52,080
You two, it's time to dash.

682
00:51:52,390 --> 00:51:53,840
- Yes, sir.
- Let's go.

683
00:51:53,870 --> 00:51:55,030
- Come on, Guy.
- Yeah.

684
00:51:55,210 --> 00:51:56,960
- Take care out there.
- Thanks.

685
00:51:57,200 --> 00:51:58,240
We're heading out.

686
00:51:58,270 --> 00:51:59,680
- Good luck.
- Bye, goodbye.

687
00:51:59,710 --> 00:52:00,710
We're off.

688
00:52:00,820 --> 00:52:01,820
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

689
00:52:13,300 --> 00:52:14,170
Hello?

690
00:52:14,210 --> 00:52:16,210
Hi, hi. Where are you now?

691
00:52:17,110 --> 00:52:18,320
Almost there. Just a bit more.

692
00:52:18,820 --> 00:52:21,200
Well, if you're late,
you might get disqualified.

693
00:52:21,420 --> 00:52:22,420
Yeah, I'll be there.

694
00:52:24,630 --> 00:52:25,630
Come.

695
00:52:26,390 --> 00:52:29,400
Oh, Dad took the bike for delivery.
What now?

696
00:52:30,100 --> 00:52:31,560
Let's just get a cab.

697
00:52:37,640 --> 00:52:39,180
Hey, he's back.

698
00:52:39,650 --> 00:52:41,960
Hey, Dad. Stop, stop.

699
00:52:41,990 --> 00:52:42,990
- Stop.
- What?

700
00:52:43,660 --> 00:52:46,520
- Get out, get out.
- Yeah, yeah. What's going on?

701
00:52:46,880 --> 00:52:48,439
Come on, we're running out of time.

702
00:52:48,440 --> 00:52:49,440
What's the rush?

703
00:52:50,670 --> 00:52:52,160
Father, I'm sorry.

704
00:52:52,190 --> 00:52:54,160
Yeah, yeah.
You're going with him, huh?

705
00:52:54,180 --> 00:52:55,240
Okay, come on.

706
00:52:55,850 --> 00:52:57,000
Easy, easy.

707
00:52:59,740 --> 00:53:01,120
- You got it?
- I got it. Hmph.

708
00:53:04,110 --> 00:53:05,110
Come on, come on.

709
00:53:09,290 --> 00:53:10,290
Let's go.

710
00:53:11,200 --> 00:53:14,400
Well... what in the world was that?

711
00:53:15,000 --> 00:53:17,320
Alright, drive safe. Take it easy.

712
00:53:18,470 --> 00:53:19,470
Oh.

713
00:53:20,770 --> 00:53:22,666
"Wedding Invitation: Anong
and Somporn" I must go now.

714
00:53:22,690 --> 00:53:24,160
Time to go pick up Anong.

715
00:53:24,260 --> 00:53:25,840
Yeah, go on.

716
00:53:26,170 --> 00:53:29,440
I don't know what came over me.
I burst into tears mid-scene.

717
00:53:29,950 --> 00:53:31,150
Nothing during rehearsal.

718
00:53:31,190 --> 00:53:35,080
I don't know either,
but while writing, I cried too.

719
00:53:35,430 --> 00:53:36,600
Are you ready, Father?

720
00:53:37,480 --> 00:53:40,200
I've been ready.
Can't wait to see clearly.

721
00:53:40,300 --> 00:53:46,239
The world keeps
turning every day.

722
00:53:46,240 --> 00:53:51,479
And we keep turning in its play.

723
00:53:51,480 --> 00:53:54,799
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

724
00:53:54,800 --> 00:53:57,439
We just might see
the world within.

725
00:53:57,440 --> 00:54:01,559
Let's walk together, day by day.

726
00:54:01,560 --> 00:54:06,600
Come take the step,
what do you say?

727
00:54:13,080 --> 00:54:16,839
Let us be real,
not dreaming away,

728
00:54:16,840 --> 00:54:20,519
We'll walk in the light
of a new day.

729
00:54:20,520 --> 00:54:25,599
No one can tell
what tomorrow may say.

730
00:54:25,600 --> 00:54:28,079
Wherever the gentle wind blows,

731
00:54:28,080 --> 00:54:30,879
let our hearts flow,
soft and slow.

732
00:54:30,880 --> 00:54:35,760
And land where
our hearts both grow.

733
00:54:36,030 --> 00:54:41,999
The world keeps
turning every day.

734
00:54:42,000 --> 00:54:47,239
And we keep turning in its play.

735
00:54:47,240 --> 00:54:50,519
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

736
00:54:50,520 --> 00:54:53,199
We just might see
the world within.

737
00:54:53,200 --> 00:54:57,279
Let's walk together, day by day.

738
00:54:57,280 --> 00:55:02,160
Come take the step,
what do you say?

